<related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " xtrc="topicref:1;7:41" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/index.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="parent" scope="local" type="concept" xtrc="topicref:5;16:39" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/userguide.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>DITA Open Toolkit Developer Reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">     <ph class="- topic/ph " xtrc="ph:1;11:30" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/index.dita">The <cite class="- topic/cite " xtrc="cite:1;11:40" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/index.dita">Developer Reference</cite> is designed to provide more advanced information about       the DITA-OT. It is geared to an audience that needs information about the DITA-OT architecture, extending the       DITA-OT, and creating DITA-OT plug-ins.</ph>   </desc></link><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " xtrc="topicref:1;7:41" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugins-overview.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="concept" xtrc="topicref:2;8:44" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Overview of plug-ins</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Plug-ins enable users to extend the functionality of the DITA-OT. This might entail adding support for     specialized document types, integrating processing overrides, or defining new output     transformations.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-xmlcatalog.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="task" xtrc="topicref:6;13:46" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Extending an XML catalog file</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">You can update either the main DITA-OT XML catalog or the XML catalog that is used by the PDF plug-in. This     enables the DITA-OT to support new specializations and document-type shells.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-anttarget.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="task" xtrc="topicref:7;14:45" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Adding a new target to the Ant build process</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Use the Ant conductor extension point (<codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrc="codeph:1;7:61" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plugin-anttarget.dita">dita.conductor.target.relative</codeph>) to make new targets     available to the Ant processing pipeline. This can be done as part of creating a new transformation, extending     pre-processing, or simply to make new Ant targets available to other plug-ins.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-antpreprocess.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="task" xtrc="topicref:8;15:49" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Adding an Ant target to the pre-processing pipeline</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">You can add an Ant target to the pre-processing pipeline. This enables you to insert additional processing     before or after the pre-processing chain or a specific step in the pre-processing operation.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-newtranstype.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="task" xtrc="topicref:9;16:48" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Adding a new transformation type</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Plug-ins can integrate an entirely new transformation type. The new transformation type can be very simple,     such as an XHTML build that creates an additional control file; it also can be very complex, adding any number of     new processing steps.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-overridestyle.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="task" xtrc="topicref:10;17:49" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Overriding an XSLT-processing step</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">You can override specific XSLT-processing steps in both the pre-processing pipeline and certain DITA-OT     transformations.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/using-plugin-URI-extension.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="task" xtrc="topicref:11;18:55" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Referencing files from other plug-ins</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Starting with DITA-OT 1.5.4, you can use the <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrc="filepath:1;6:10" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/using-plugin-URI-extension.dita">plugin:<varname class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname " xtrc="varname:1;6:26" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/using-plugin-URI-extension.dita">plugin-id</varname></filepath> URI extension and the <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrc="filepath:2;7:10" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/using-plugin-URI-extension.dita">${dita.plugin.<varname class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname " xtrc="varname:2;7:33" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/using-plugin-URI-extension.dita">plugin-id</varname>.dir}</filepath> Ant variable to reference the     base path of another installed DITA-OT plug-in.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-addgeneratedtext.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="reference" xtrc="topicref:12;19:52" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Modifying or adding generated text</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Generated text is the term for strings that are automatically added by the build, such as "Note" before the     contents of a &lt;note&gt; element.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-xsltparams.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="task" xtrc="topicref:13;20:46" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Adding parameters to existing XSLT steps</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">You can pass parameters from the Ant build to existing XSLT steps in both the pre-processing pipeline and     certain DITA-OT transformations. This can be useful if you want to make the parameters available as global       <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:1;9:19" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plugin-xsltparams.dita">xsl:param</xmlelement> values within XSLT overrides.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-javalib.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="task" xtrc="topicref:14;21:43" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Adding a Java library to the DITA-OT classpath parameter</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">You can use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrc="codeph:1;7:38" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plugin-javalib.dita">dita.conductor.lib.import</codeph> extension point to add an additional Java     library to the DITA-OT <parmname class="+ topic/keyword pr-d/parmname " xtrc="parmname:2;8:38" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plugin-javalib.dita">classpath</parmname> parameter.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-messages.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="task" xtrc="topicref:15;22:44" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Adding new diagnostic messages</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrc="codeph:1;7:30" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plugin-messages.dita">dita.xsl.messages</codeph> extension point to add plug-in-specific messages to the     diagnostic messages that are generated by the DITA-OT. These messages then can be used by any XSLT     override.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-newextensions.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="reference" xtrc="topicref:16;23:49" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Creating a new plug-in extension point</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">If your plug-in needs to define its own extension point in an XML file, add the string       "<codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrc="codeph:1;8:16" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plugin-newextensions.dita">_template</codeph>" to the filename before the file suffix. During integration, this file will be     processed like the built-in DITA-OT templates.</desc></link><link class="- topic/link " format="dita" href="../dev_ref/plugin-sample.dita" mapclass="- map/topicref " role="child" scope="local" type="reference" xtrc="topicref:17;24:42" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plug-ins.ditamap"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Example plugin.xml file</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">The following is a sample of a <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrc="filepath:1;7:55" xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/plugin-sample.dita">plugin.xml</filepath> file. This file adds support for a new set     of specialized DTDs, and includes an override for the XHTML output processor.</desc></link></linkpool></linkpool></related-links></task>